25|$|Both Moscow and St. Petersburg have {{memorials}} to {{the victims}} of <b>the</b> <b>Gulag</b> made of boulders from the Solovki camp — the first prison camp in <b>the</b> <b>Gulag</b> system. Moscow's memorial is on Lubyanka Square, the site of the headquarters of the NKVD. People gather at these memorials every year on the Day of Victims of the Repression (October 30).|$|E
