50|$|Due to {{the fact}} that Ukrainians were {{prominent}} in <b>the</b> <b>Gulags</b> of Norilsk and Vorkuta Ukrainians have continued to be the majority ethnicity in these cities. Around 80% of the population in Norilsk in 1989 had least one Ukrainian ancestor.|$|R
25|$|Anne Applebaum, a Pulitzer Prize winner, {{carried out}} an {{extensive}} investigation of <b>the</b> <b>gulags,</b> and {{explained in a}} lecture in 2003, that it's extremely difficult not only to document the facts given {{the extent of the}} cover-up but to bring the truth home.|$|R
